    "Additionally, larger networks have the risk of overfitting when training data is limited.",
    "On the other hand, by comparing the performance of models on cracks of different sizes, we found that predicting smaller cracks is more challenging than larger ones.",
    "In Fig. 9, the accuracies of the models trained with the unnormalized dataset are shown.",
    "To show the influence of crack size to the performance, the results for the whole test set as well as for the adjusted test set of excluding smaller cracks are given.",
    "For larger cracks, the differences in the performance (e.g., accuracy) among different models (including various encoder networks and no decoder versions) are minimal."
